comments.body:
@rhatdan for the `-f -` case, podman creates a scratch context directory `$TMPDIR/buildahXXXXXXX`. I would like to consider that a corner case of a corner case, stick my head in the sand, la-la-la, pretend it doesn't exist. For `-f /path/to/Containerfile`, I have confirmed multiple times that podman uses `/path/to` as its context directory. (I have not tested podman-remote).

@vyasgun, good question, and I may not be the right person to answer that. I have a moderate (70-80%) predilection for keeping the square brackets because to me seeing `ARG` in help/manpage is strongly indicative that `ARG` is mandatory: that there is no situation in which `ARG` can be skipped. Seeing brackets does not tell me "you can omit it", it tells me "_there are situations_ in which you can omit it". A subtle distinction but, I think, an important one for a reader.

But that's just my preference. Others in the @containers/podman-maintainers team may have different opinions, and theirs will carry more weight than mine.
